/docs/environment/definitions/.body: Environment Definitions and Acronyms Term or Acronym Definition Application The generic name given to a project that uses Origen Origen A general purpose semiconductor engineering framework that uses the Ruby programming language, read more at http://origen.freescale.net

/docs/environment/installation/.title: Installation
/docs/environment/installation/.subtitle: Environment
/docs/environment/installation/.body:
Environment Installation Follow the steps below to setup a new environment. 1. Install Origen Follow these instructions to install Origen: How to Install Origen 2. Create the application workspace This workspace must be situated outside of the Origen workspace that you have just created. Execute the following commands: mkdir origen_core
cd origen_core
dssc setvault .
dssc pop -rec -uni -get -force -ver 0.0.5 .
